file:        c5_slave_merged.bin
chip:        esp32c5
flash-size:  4 MB
flash-mode:  dio
flash-freq:  80 MHz
flash-at:    0x0
size-bytes:  1585280
size-human:  1.5 MB
sha256:      0de1afbab328021723747c638730226903185e67ca81e5fde69a5c71c1af9c40

upstream:    https://github.com/espressif/esp-hosted-mcu @ f99ee55aea93ab671d9849bd962aa2f10d01f7d5
idf:         v6.0
target:      esp32c5

phy-hack:
  - phy_11p_set(1, 0) armed at boot and on every WIFI_EVENT_WIFI_READY
  - country set to "01" with WIFI_COUNTRY_POLICY_MANUAL (allows ITS channels)
  - bootstrap channel = 140, then phy_change_channel(180, 1, 0, 0)
  - WIFI_PS_NONE
  - phy_agc_max_gain_set(255), phy_disable_low_rate()

custom-rpcs:
  Bound to esp-hosted's peer-data channel (CONFIG_ESP_HOSTED_ENABLE_PEER_DATA_TRANSFER).
  Host calls esp_hosted_open_*; matching handlers run on the slave.
  msg_id namespace: 0xC1750000 + ...

  Channel / band / freq:
    SET_CHANNEL, SET_FREQ, SET_BAND, SET_BANDWIDTH, SET_CHAN_FILT,
    SET_CHAN14_MIC, SET_COUNTRY_PERM
  PHY mode / rate:
    SET_PHY_11P, SET_RATE, SET_LOW_RATE
  TX power:
    SET_TX_POWER, SET_MOST_TPW, GET_MOST_TPW
  RX gain / AGC:
    SET_RX_GAIN, SET_AGC_MAX_GAIN, RESET_RX_GAIN_TBL
  CCA / channel-busy:
    SET_CCA, GET_CCA_COUNTERS, RESET_CCA_COUNT
  Diagnostics:
    GET_PHY_RSSI, GET_NOISE_FLOOR, GET_TEMPERATURE
  CSI / loopback:
    SET_CSI_DUMP, SET_LOOPBACK
  BT-radio (nRF24-style hacks):
    SET_BT_TX_GAIN, SET_BT_FILTER
  Meta:
    GET_INFO, GET_CAPS

  Raw 802.11 + 2.4 GHz:
    TX_80211, SET_PROMISC, SET_PROMISC_FILTER, SET_PROTOCOL, SET_MAC,
    SET_CSI_ENABLE, FTM_INITIATE

  ESP-NOW (universal):
    ESPNOW_INIT, ESPNOW_DEINIT, ESPNOW_ADD_PEER, ESPNOW_DEL_PEER,
    ESPNOW_SEND, ESPNOW_SET_PMK

  802.15.4 (Thread / Zigbee — NOT_SUPPORTED on C5; works on C6/H2/H4):
    IEEE154_ENABLE, IEEE154_SET_CHAN, IEEE154_SET_PANID,
    IEEE154_SET_PROMISC, IEEE154_TX_RAW

  Async events (slave -> host):
    OCB_FRAME, PHY_STATE, RAW_FRAME, CSI, FTM_REPORT,
    ESPNOW_RX, ESPNOW_TX_STATUS, IEEE154_RX

bluetooth-le:
  Already exposed by upstream esp-hosted-mcu — see
  vendor/esp-hosted-mcu/host/esp_hosted_bt.h (HCI bridge) and
  vendor/esp-hosted-mcu/host/esp_hosted_bluedroid.h (Bluedroid).

defaults:
  - channel:   CCH (180, 5.900 GHz)
  - tx-gated:  off (slave does not emit; host is responsible)
